      <!-- In the Press -->
      <mj-wrapper background-color="#f5f5f5" padding="0 0 15">
        <mj-section padding="10 0" background-color="#fff" border-radius="3">
          <mj-column>
            <mj-text align="left" font-size="20" color="#4A4A4A" font-weight="700" padding-bottom="0">In the Press</mj-text>
            <mj-text align="left" font-size="14" color="#4A4A4A" font-weight="400" padding-top="0">
              <p>
                The Nation <a href="https://www.thenation.com/article/the-secret-to-progressives-electoral-success/" target="_blank">credited</a> Somerville's local Our Revolution chapter with doing "the real work" of elections. The Huffington Post
                <a
                  href="https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/lee-carter-delegate-democratic-socialist_us_5a074548e4b05673aa5997fd" target="_blank">covered</a> Lee Carter's victory in Virginia noting the "20,000 doors his campaign reached in the final four days before the election." The New Republic <a href="https://newrepublic.com/article/145739/left-great-election-night-will-democrats-take-advantage"
                    target="_blank">highlighted</a> the "slew of local candidates backed by Our Revolution" who won "city council seats in Knoxville, Tennessee; Charlottesville, Virginia, and Somerville, Massachusetts."
              </p>
            </mj-text>
          </mj-column>
